{
  "stem": "7302.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't think we'll make it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we run-- we even didn't know where we're running.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We have been running like sheeps.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Our destination was we going to Kiev, because Kiev in our mind was-- it's a big city.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it's a Jewish-- lots of Jewish live there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it's never happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Instead to kill, we went to-- near [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] It survived only my older sister, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like we have been three sisters after the brothers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No one from my brothers survived.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No one from all the sister from the other mother survived-- and her kids.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's only us who-- who went with the trains, who have been left.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In Polona, I told you, they was saying they will go next day with the horses farther.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They-- they started to bomb.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When we left, they started to bomb-- nothing left of the city at all there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Everyone was killed who was there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that's it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You wanted to know about my sisters.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my oldest sister, [NON-ENGLISH], and her husband with a little boy have been-- we have been all the time together-- and my younger sister with her husband.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was born-- my older sister was born another child during the war, a girl.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the other sister was having a-- a boy, and a son and a daughter.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They live in Israel.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my older sister lived in Canada.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I didn't tell you how after the war, how they got.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Maybe my husband did tell you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[SIGHS] When I went to Kiev, I have been working there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And my mind was-- I will take them out from this place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it's happened in 1945 that-- that people could emigrate already.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They could go places, you know?",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
